    "en": {
      "title": "An automatic sterilizer from the Army",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "An automatic hand sanitizer machine produced by the Army's Research, Analysis and Development Unit was introduced to President Gotabaya Rajapaksa this morning (06th) at the Presidential Office.",
        "The machine has the capacity to disinfect the hands of 600 people by storing four liters of disinfectant liquid and can operate automatically for forty-eight hours after charging.",
        "It is possible to manufacture this machine in the country at low cost compared to import. Therefore, the Army Research Unit is ready to produce the machines for the orders received and to provide the knowledge about it to the interested parties.",
        "Army Commander and Chief of Defense Staff General Shavendra Silva, Additional Secretary to the President Major General (Retired) K.B. Mr. Egodawele and Brigadier Sudath Udayasena were present on this occasion."
      ],
